      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-13T17:33:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I assume you would be creating a GrDawnTextureRenderTarget here? The model of all our other backends is that this logic would live out in the Gr*Gpu class, and would call a TextureRenderTarget::Make factory. My worry is that once you start handling multisampling and all the other stuff needed for TextureRenderTarget, this factory could get complicated and hard to read with lots of if (renderable) statements.\n\nBut if in the end you think it does workout better and looks cleaner/easier to read doing it this way I\u0027m not against it.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 71,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 72,
        "endChar": 35
      },
      "revId": "0eeb00c6e652929745d991c76befeb48370a9d0e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
